description: A group of 21 retired judges of the Supreme Court and high courts have written to the Chief Justice of India on the escalating attempts by "certain factions to undermine the judiciary through calculated pressure, misinformation, and public disparagement". The list includes names of former judges from Gujarat, Delhi, Rajasthan, Sikkim, Jharkhand, Mumbai, Allahabad, Uttrakhand, Punjab and Haryana, and Madhya Pradesh High Courts.
title: Retired judges write to CJI against attempts to 'undermine' judiciary

description: Mumbai Indians captain Hardik Pandya is under scrutiny again after a 20-run loss against Chennai Super Kings in the ongoing Indian Premier League. Despite a brief resurgence, the team's performance intensified pressure on Pandya, particularly after being hit by Dhoni for three consecutive sixes, leading to dissatisfaction among the Wankhede faithful.
title: 'Ordinary bowling, ordinary captaincy': Hardik under fire

description: In Noida, a student  was brutally assaulted by young men. A viral video captured the attack, leading to police action and arrests. The motive behind the assault remains under investigation, sparking public outrage.
title: Noida student dragged out of car and thrashed, video viral

description: Australian cricket legend Brett Lee predicts Team India will be the frontrunners for the 2024 T20 World Cup title, despite their loss in the ICC ODI World Cup final at home. The tournament is scheduled to start from June 2 in the US and West Indies. India won the T20 World Cup in the inaugural edition in 2007.
title: Exclusive: Brett Lee on Rohit-led Team India's T20 WC chances

description: Indian workers in Tel Aviv remain calm despite war fears. They celebrated festivals and stayed prepared for emergencies, including possible return to India if necessary.
title: Indian workers in Israel unperturbed as country comes under Iranian attack

description: Rohit Sharma's heroic unbeaten 105 fell short as Mumbai Indians lost by 20 runs against Chennai Super Kings. CSK's captain Ruturaj Gaikwad hailed MS Dhoni as a "young wicket-keeper", whose explosive cameo sealed the victory. Dhoni's quickfire 20, including three sixes, bolstered CSK's total to 206/4, backed by strong performances from Shivam Dube and Gaikwad.
title: 'A young wicket-keeper…': Gaikwad's cheeky take on Dhoni's impact

description: Mumbai Indians lost to Chennai Super Kings in the IPL 2024 match, despite Rohit Sharma's unbeaten 105 off 63 balls. The Mumbai Indians couldn't chase down Chennai Super Kings' total, resulting in a 20-run defeat. MS Dhoni consoled Rohit Sharma after the contest, showcasing camaraderie and mutual respect between players.
title: A heartwarming moment! MS Dhoni consoles Rohit Sharma

description: Chikkaballapur LS seat includes Foxconn, industrial zones. Candidates promise water solution, hi-tech flower market. BJP seeks JD(S) support. Ramaiah inexperienced; Sudhakar ex-MLA. PM Modi's popularity, caste votes influential. Congress focuses on guarantees, caste votes.
title: Karnataka: Caste, guarantees may trump party calculations

description: Tesla has signed a strategic deal with Tata Electronics to acquire semiconductor chips, signaling its interest in India's automotive market. The agreement positions Tata as a key supplier for global clients entering India's semiconductor value chain. Elon Musk plans to visit India for potential investments in electric vehicle manufacturing facilities, estimated at $2-3 billion.
title: 'Tesla signs deal with Tata Electronics for semiconductor chips'

description: Mumbai Indians' batting coach, Kieron Pollard, has defended Hardik Pandya after criticism for his performance in the IPL match against Chennai Super Kings. Pollard emphasized that cricket is a team game and called for support rather than criticism. He expressed confidence in Pandya's abilities and his crucial role in India's upcoming T20 World Cup.
title: 'I am sick and fed up…': Pollard defends Hardik amidst criticism

description: Zomato has outperformed all other companies in a Bloomberg Intelligence index of global ride sharing and delivery peers in terms of price target upgrades over the past year. Recently, several brokerages, including "Citigroup Inc and HSBC Holdings Plc," have raised their estimates for the stock. The shares of Zomato have skyrocketed by nearly 260% since April of the previous year, making it challenging for consensus to keep pace.
title: Why analysts are playing catch up with this delivery stock

description: India has emerged as the most favored investment destination among the three major Asian economies, according to a recent MLIV Pulse survey. Despite China's low stock valuations and Japan's efforts to enhance corporate governance, nearly half of the 390 respondents chose India as the top pick. The survey results reflect a strong belief in the potential of Indian companies, as the country prepares for its general elections, which will be held in seven phases from April 19 to June 1.
title: Why ‘expensive’ Indian stocks are set to beat cheap China equities

description: Biden has expressed concerns over Israel-Iran escalation and has urged restraint.  This comes in the wake of Iran's recent missile and drone attacks on Israel, which marked a significant escalation in the conflict. The attacks were reportedly in retaliation for an Israeli drone strike in Syria that resulted in the deaths of 12 Iranians, including two high-ranking generals.
title: Iran attack on Israel: Biden privately fears 'catastrophic escalation'

description: Of the 220+ IT businesses they host, Mangaluru & Udupi cities added 40 in the past year alone
title: How two Karnataka cities are raring to scale IT growth

description: Finance Ministry proposes measures to combat cyber fraud post Bank of Baroda World app scam. Urgency highlighted by 1.1M cyber fraud cases in 2023. Efforts include National Crime Records Bureau data, Indian Cyber Crime Coordination Centre formation, and inter-ministerial meeting.
title: RBI ban on BOB World app: Fin min's plans to deal with frauds

description: Cricket bowlers adapt strategies in the IPL, focusing on three-quarter length balls over yorkers. Players like Suryakumar Yadav challenge bowlers to hit top of off to prevent boundaries, leading to varied bowling approaches for success. With wickets getting more tired with increased traffic on them as the season wears on, expect the delivery to yield more dividends for bowlers.
title: IPL 2024: Is the length ball more valuable than the yorker?

description: Bollywood superstar Salman Khan's Mumbai house - Galaxy Apartment faced gunshots on April 14, initiating a thorough investigation. The incident stirred concern, leading to increased security measures. As details emerged, solidarity from the Bollywood community and the transfer of the case to the Mumbai Crime Branch showcased the gravity of the situation.
title: Firing outside Salman house: Here's complete timeline of incident

description: Enclave dwellers in India face long-standing land ownership issues post the 2015 exchange with Bangladesh, impacting their legal status and election dynamics. Political parties are involved, but resolution through a land tribunal process is anticipated in the coming months.
title: No man’s land: Enclave dwellers stuck in a limbo

description: Australian police said Monday they are investigating why a 40-year-old man with mental illness appeared to target women as he roamed a Sydney shopping mall with a large knife, killing six people and injuring a dozen more. The only man killed was 30-year-old Pakistani man Faraz Tahir, who had been working as a security guard when he was stabbed.
title: Sydney mall attack: Police probes attacker's motive of targeting woman

description: Kerala leads in women's empowerment but lacks female political representation. UDF, LDF, NDA vie for women voters. Urban women tilt towards UDF. Muslim women's votes split. NDA focuses on youth support.
title: In the shadows, but women hold Kerala key

description: Kerala leads in women's empowerment but lacks female political representation. UDF, LDF, NDA vie for women voters. Urban women tilt towards UDF. Muslim women's votes split. NDA focuses on youth support.
title: In the shadows, but women hold Kerala key

description: MS Dhoni returned to Mumbai for CSK's IPL 2024 match, visited BCCI headquarters, admired the ODI World Cup trophy, and signed iconic photographs. In the match against Mumbai Indians, Dhoni's 20 runs off four balls secured Chennai Super Kings' victory. On Sunday after the MI-CSK match, BCCI released a heart-warming video that shows Dhoni at the headquarters.
title: Watch: MS Dhoni with 2011 ODI and 2007 T20 World Cup trophies
